# Database Rules

## Core Rule

The database is the source of truth.

All database-related work must be done carefully, reviewed, and reproducible.

---

## 1. Supabase / Database Access Must Be Read-Only by Default

Cursor must use Supabase/database access for inspection only.

Allowed:
- inspect schemas
- inspect tables
- inspect columns
- inspect views
- inspect indexes
- run SELECT queries
- check relationships
- check existing data shape

Not allowed directly:
- CREATE
- ALTER
- DROP
- INSERT
- UPDATE
- DELETE
- TRUNCATE

Cursor must not directly modify the real database.

---

## 2. Always Inspect the Real Database First

Before generating any database-related code, Cursor must inspect the current real database state.

Check:
- existing schemas
- existing table columns
- existing view definitions
- existing indexes
- foreign keys
- geometry columns
- SRID
- current sample rows when needed

Never assume table names, column names, or view definitions.

---

## 3. Always Generate Migration Files

All database changes must be written as migration files first.

Do not apply database changes directly from Cursor.

Migration files should be placed in:

```text
infrastructure/database/migrations/